eam 3M|language=French|trans-title=Kevin Van Hoovels, latest recruit for Team 3M|work=Directvelo|publisher=Association Le Peloton|date=18 November 2013|accessdate=24 December 2013|first=Renaud|last=Collette}}</ref> and in mountain biking for the Versluys team.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nieuwsblad.be/sportwereld/cnt/dmf20131118_00843957|title=Kevin Van Hoovels verlengt contract bij Team Versluys, wegprogramma bij Team3M|language=Dutch|trans-title=Kevin Van Hoovels extends contract with Team Versluys, road programme at Team3M|work=Sportwereld\u2013[[Het Nieuwsblad]]|publisher=[[Corelio]]|date=18 November 2013|accessdate=24 December 2013|agency=[[Belga (news agency)|Belga]]}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2012}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Van Hoovels, Kevin}}\n[[Category:Belgian male cyclists]]\n[[Category:Cross-country mountain bikers]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Olympic cyclists of Belgium]]\n[[Category:Cyclists at the 2012 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:1985 births]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Antwerp (province)]]\n[[Category:People from Bonheiden]]\n{{Belgium-cycling-bio-1980s-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox cyclist\n| name          = Kevin Van Hoovels\n| image         = Kevin-van-hoovels-1336076724.jpg\n| caption       = Van Hoovels in 2012\n| fullname      = Kevin Van Hoovels\n| nickname      =\n| birth_date    = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1985|7|31}}\n| birth_place   = [[Bonheiden]], [[Belgium]]\n| height        =\n| weight        =\n| currentteam   = Team3M ''(road)''<br>Team Versluys ''(MTB)''\n| discipline    = MTB and road\n| role          = Rider\n| ridertype     =\n| amateuryears1 = 2005\n| amateurteam1  = {{ct|JVC|2005}}\n| amateuryears2 = 2010\u2013\n| amateurteam2  = Lingier-Versluys ''(MTB)''\n| proyears1     = 2012\u20132013\n| proteam1      = [[Ventilair-Steria|Bofrost-Steria]]\n| proyears2     = 2014\u2013\n| proteam2      = [[Team 3M]]\n| majorwins     =\n}}\n'''Kevin Van Hoovels''' (born 31 July 1985) is a Belgian cross-country mountain biker. At the [[2012 Summer Olympics]], he competed in the [[Cycling at the 2012 Summer Olympics&nbsp;\u2013 Men's cross-country|Men's cross-country]] at [[Hadleigh Farm]], finishing in 19th place.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.london2012.com/athlete/van-hoovels-kevin-1128995/events/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120804035209/http://www.london2012.com/athlete/van-hoovels-kevin-1128995/events/|url-status=dead|archive-date=4 August 2012|title=Kevin van Hoovels|publisher=London 2012|accessdate=13 September 2012}}</ref>\n\nHe became widely known on the internet for his immediate reaction after losing a sprint finish during a race.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=knyB1p_TgCs|title=Kevin van Hoovels cries like a baby|publisher=Youtube|accessdate=22 July 2012}}</ref>\n\nFor the 2014 season, Van Hoovels is competing on the roads for Team3M,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.directvelo.com/actualite/30749-kevin-van-hoovels-derniere-recrue-du-team-3m.html|title=Kevin Van Hoovels, derni\u00e8re recrue du Team 3M|language=French|trans-title=Kevin Van Hoovels, latest recruit for Team 3M|work=Directvelo|publisher=Association Le Peloton|date=18 November 2013|accessdate=24 December 2013|first=Renaud|last=Collette}}</ref> and in mountain biking for the Versluys team.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nieuwsblad.be/sportwereld/cnt/dmf20131118_00843957|title=Kevin Van Hoovels verlengt contract bij Team Versluys, wegprogramma bij Team3M|language=Dutch|trans-title=Kevin Van Hoovels extends contract with Team Versluys, road programme at Team3M|work=Sportwereld\u2013[[Het Nieuwsblad]]|publisher=[[Corelio]]|date=18 November 2013|accessdate=24 December 2013|agency=[[Belga (news agency)|Belga]]}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2012}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Van Hoovels, Kevin}}\n[[Category:Belgian male cyclists]]\n[[Category:Cross-country mountain bikers]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:O